                            <comment id="237932" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 4 Dec 2018 18:55:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently ZFS 0.8.0-rc2 build fails via lbuild because we aren&apos;t building pyzfs and we have python-cffi installed on build machines so python is enabled by configure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed a fix upstream:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/zfsonlinux/zfs/pull/8179&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;zfs pull 8179&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;EDIT:&lt;/b&gt; There is a more comprehensive fix for this issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/zfsonlinux/zfs/pull/8096&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;ZFS pull 8096&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
