                            <comment id="233974" author="adilger" created="Tue, 25 Sep 2018 14:36:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Even if we don&apos;t have a 0.8.0 release available before Lustre 2.12 is released, it would be good if we can at least get the code building with 0.8.0-rc1 so that when it is inevitably released people will be able to test it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="233972" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 25 Sep 2018 13:58:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For direct compilation&#160;&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;(autopen.sh &amp;amp;&amp;amp; ./configure ...) we just need 0.7.11 support (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11393&quot; title=&quot;Update ZFS Version to 0.7.11&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11393&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11393&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). &#160;lbuild needs to be updated, unless we can use rpms from ZoL.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;Building against ZoL provided rpms works fine locally. lbuild will still need to do obnoxious things with unpacking and placing.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;Current status as of ZFS 0.8.0-rc1:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;m4 scripts are fine (given &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11393&quot; title=&quot;Update ZFS Version to 0.7.11&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11393&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11393&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fix)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;lbuild definitely needs work&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;man pages are fine&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;dkms spec DOES need spl removal (which should be fine for pre 0.8.0 releases since zfs requires spl prior to that)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Debian build is fine (spl still exists, but is provided by zfs rpms)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="233686" author="adilger" created="Tue, 18 Sep 2018 15:14:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How are we doing with the idea of using the upstream ZFS RPM packages for lustre-patchless?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
